citation.case_name: East Lake Land Co. v. Brown

html:
155 U.S. 488

15 S.Ct. 357

39 L.Ed. 233

EAST LAKE LAND CO.
v.
BROWN.

No. 121.

December 17, 1894.

John T. Morgan, for plaintiff in error.

D. P. Bestor, for defendant in error.

Mr. Chief Justice FULLER.

1

The judgment is reversed, with costs, and the case remanded, with a direction to remand it to the city court of Birmingham, county of Jefferson, Ala., on the authority of Chappell v. Waterworth, 155 U. S. 102, 15 Sup. Ct. 34.

2

Reversed and remanded.

The judgment is reversed with costs, and the case remanded with a direction to remand it to the City Court of Birmingham, county of Jefferson, Alabama, on the authority of Chappell v. Waterworth, 155 U.S. 102.

Reversed and remanded.
